### PHONE VERIFICATION ENDPOINTS

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@phoneNumber = +2348072496614
@phoneOtp = 654321


### 1. Send Phone OTP
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/send-phone-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneNumber}}"
}

### Expected Response (Success):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "message": "OTP sent successfully to your phone",
#   "expiresIn": "10 minutes"
# }

### Expected Response (Already Verified):
# {
#   "statusCode": 400,
#   "message": "Phone number is already verified",
#   "error": "Bad Request"
# }

### Expected Response (User Not Found):
# {
#   "statusCode": 404,
#   "message": "User not found with this phone number",
#   "error": "Not Found"
# }

### Expected Response (Rate Limited):
# {
#   "statusCode": 400,
#   "message": "Please wait 45 seconds before requesting a new OTP",
#   "error": "Bad Request"
# }


### 2. Verify Phone OTP
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/verify-phone-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "{{phoneNumber}}",
  "otp": "{{phoneOtp}}"
}

### Expected Response (Success):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "message": "Phone number verified successfully",
#   "isVerified": true
# }

### Expected Response (Invalid OTP):
# {
#   "statusCode": 400,
#   "message": "Invalid OTP. Please check and try again",
#   "error": "Bad Request"
# }

### Expected Response (Expired OTP):
# {
#   "statusCode": 400,
#   "message": "OTP has expired. Please request a new one",
#   "error": "Bad Request"
# }

### Expected Response (No OTP Found):
# {
#   "statusCode": 400,
#   "message": "No OTP found. Please request a new OTP",
#   "error": "Bad Request"
# }


### 3. Check Phone Status
GET {{baseUrl}}/verification/phone-status?phoneNumber={{phoneNumber}}

### Expected Response (Verified):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "isVerified": true,
#   "phoneNumber": "+1234567890"
# }

### Expected Response (Not Verified):
# {
#   "success": true,
#   "isVerified": false,
#   "phoneNumber": "+1234567890"
# }


### TEST SCENARIOS

### Complete Phone Verification Flow

### Step 1: Send Phone OTP
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/send-phone-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567890"
}

### Step 2: Verify Phone (check SMS for OTP)
POST {{baseUrl}}/verification/verify-phone-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phoneNumber": "+1234567890",
  "otp": "654321"
}

### Step 3: Check Phone Statuse
GET {{baseUrl}}/verification/phone-status?phoneNumber=+1234567890


